-- Obama to give address on debt limit at 9 p.m. ET
-- 
-- Mon Jul 25, 2011 4:37pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/25/us-usa-debt-obama-speech-idUSTRE76O5T320110725

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - President Barack Obama will deliver remarks at 9 p.m. EDT on Monday (0100 GMT on Tuesday) about the state of efforts to raise the government's debt ceiling, the White House said in a statement. 

 "The president will address the nation from the White House on the stalemate in Washington over avoiding default and the best approach to cutting deficits," it said. (Reporting by  Caren Bohan  and  Laura MacInnis )